      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "The Holt yard have a grip on this race with four leading chances including two unbeaten youngsters. BETTER BLITZEM (1) is a speedy colt who won both starts in first campaign and returns from a break. Aided Holt stays aboard and the colt has posted the best figures of this field. With further upside should go close again. Stablemate GONE COUNTRY (3) has the fitness edge though and will be tough to beat. Has won both starts so far showing good pace and drops 4kg for beating some of these last time. Low draw and will take catching. DUB STEPPING (2) returned from a break with leading rider Ryan Wiggins aboard and scored a strong win. Fitter again and will stalk the pace but does need to lift his figures to match the other pair. TAMBO'S SISTER (6) is another Holt runner who was heavily bet on debut when fourth behind the stablemate GONE COUNTRY. Was very green and is sure to have improved. The fourth stable runner SCARLENA (4) has placed 3/3 and will wind up late.",
